The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 3: The communication ministry has given a clean chit to Vodafone, saying that no licencing condition was violated by the company. As far as we are concerned, Vodafone did not violate any licencing condition and a decision is expected at the next meeting of the Foreign Investment Promotion Board (fipb), D.S. Mathur, secretary, department of telecom (DoT), said.

 Mumbai, April 3: Sebi has proposed a price band of 20 per cent on relisting of securities in cases other than initial public offers (IPOs). It has framed a draft policy for fixing the base price for start of trading in stocks belonging to non-ipo cases.

 Calcutta, April 3: Allahabad Bank has announced a rate hike on deposits of all maturities. The maximum rate is 9.50 per cent per annum for the deposit rate of one year to less than two years.

 New Delhi, April 3: European Aviation, Defence and Space Company (eads) will invest in an engineering centre in India to develop aviation softwares and aircraft designs for its planes and other systems.

 Mumbai, April 3: Orchid Chemicals and Pharmaceuticals plans to enter the Canadian generic formulations market as it has received approval from that countrys therapeutic product directorate for two of its drug applications.




